### Articles API Test - Get Article by Title with Authorization
### This file contains HTTP requests to test the protected endpoint

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5212
@username = admin
@password = password123
@articleTitle = test

### Step 1: Test API Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Test/health

### Step 2: Login to get JWT Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/Auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{username}}",
  "password": "{{password}}"
}

### Step 3: Get Article by Title (Protected - Requires Authorization)
### Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE with the token from Step 2
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Articles/title/{{articleTitle}}
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Step 4: Get All Articles (No Authorization Required)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Articles?pageNumber=1&pageSize=5

### Step 5: Validate Token
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/Auth/validate
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Alternative: Get Article by Title with different title
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Articles/title/Sample Article
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Alternative: Test with invalid token (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Articles/title/{{articleTitle}}
Authorization: Bearer invalid_token_here

### Alternative: Test without authorization header (should return 401)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/Articles/title/{{articleTitle}}

### Instructions:
### 1. Run Step 1 to verify API is running
### 2. Run Step 2 to get JWT token
### 3. Copy the "token" value from Step 2 response
### 4. Replace "YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE" in Step 3 with the actual token
### 5. Run Step 3 to test the protected endpoint
### 6. Run Step 4 to see all available articles
### 7. Run Step 5 to validate your token